# Creating a New Tool in Hypercho OS

This guide explains how to create a new tool from scratch, following the established patterns in the codebase.

## Overview

A tool in Hypercho OS consists of several components:

1. **Tool Component** - The main UI component (`components/Tool/[ToolName]/index.tsx`)
2. **Provider** - State management and app schema (`components/Tool/[ToolName]/provider/[toolName]Provider.tsx`)
3. **Page** - Next.js page wrapper (`pages/Tool/[ToolName].tsx`)
4. **OS Integration** - Registration in OSProv and VirtualRouter
5. **Virtual Component** - For instant navigation (`components/Tool/VirtualToolComponents.tsx`)

## Step-by-Step Guide

### 1. Create Tool Component Structure

Create the following directory structure:

```
components/Tool/[ToolName]/
├── index.tsx                    # Main tool component
├── provider/
│   └── [toolName]Provider.tsx   # State management provider
└── components/                  # Tool-specific components (optional)
    └── [ComponentName].tsx
```

#### Main Tool Component (`index.tsx`)

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { InteractApp } from "@OS/InteractApp";
import { use[ToolName] } from "./provider/[toolName]Provider";
import [MainComponent] from "./components/[MainComponent]";

const [ToolName] = () => {
  const { appSchema } = use[ToolName]();
  return (
    <InteractApp appSchema={appSchema}>
      <[MainComponent] />
    </InteractApp>
  );
};

export default [ToolName];
```

#### Provider (`provider/[toolName]Provider.tsx`)

```tsx
import {
  createContext,
  useContext,
  ReactNode,
  useMemo,
} from "react";
import { AppSchema, defaultAppSchema } from "@OS/Layout/types";

interface [ToolName]ContextValue {
  appSchema: AppSchema;
  // Add other state/functions as needed
}

const initialState: [ToolName]ContextValue = {
  appSchema: defaultAppSchema,
  // Initialize other values
};

const [ToolName]Context = createContext<[ToolName]ContextValue>(initialState);

export function [ToolName]Provider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  const appSchema: AppSchema = useMemo(() => {
    return {
      sidebar: {
        sections: [
          // Define sidebar sections if needed
        ],
      },
      // Add dialogs, detail panels, etc. as needed
    };
  }, []);

  const value: [ToolName]ContextValue = {
    appSchema,
    // Add other values
  };

  return (
    <[ToolName]Context.Provider value={value}>
      {children}
    </[ToolName]Context.Provider>
  );
}

export function use[ToolName]() {
  const context = useContext([ToolName]Context);
  if (context === undefined) {
    throw new Error("use[ToolName] must be used within a [ToolName]Provider");
  }
  return context;
}
```

### 2. Create Next.js Page

Create `pages/Tool/[ToolName].tsx`:

```tsx
import React from "react";
import { getLayout } from "../../layouts/MainLayout";
import { CopanionProvider } from "@OS/Provider/CopanionProv";
import { SEOSchema } from "@OS/Provider/SEOProv";
import [ToolName] from "$/components/Tool/[ToolName]";
import { [ToolName]Provider } from "$/components/Tool/[ToolName]/provider/[toolName]Provider";

const [toolName]SEOSchema: SEOSchema = {
  title: "[Tool Name] - Copanion OS",
  description: "[Tool description]",
  url: "https://www.app.claw.hypercho.com/Tool/[ToolName]",
  image: "https://hypercho.com/hypercho_banner.png",
  author: "Hypercho",
  robots: "index,follow",
  type: "software",
  themeColor: "#000319",
  // Add Twitter, OpenGraph, jsonLd as needed
};

const Index = () => {
  return (
    <CopanionProvider seoSchema={[toolName]SEOSchema}>
      <[ToolName]Provider>
        <[ToolName] />
      </[ToolName]Provider>
    </CopanionProvider>
  );
};

Index.getLayout = getLayout;
export default Index;
```

### 3. Register in OSProv

#### 3.1 Add to OSSettings Interface

In `OS/Provider/OSProv.tsx`, add to `OSSettings` interface:

```tsx
export interface OSSettings {
  // ... existing settings
  [toolName]: boolean;
}
```

#### 3.2 Add to defaultOSSettings

```tsx
const defaultOSSettings: OSSettings = {
  // ... existing defaults
  [toolName]: false,
};
```

#### 3.3 Add Context Type (if needed for widget)

If the tool needs to be a draggable widget (like TodoList, Music Player), add:

```tsx
// In the context types section
type [ToolName]ContextType = BaseWidgetContextType;

const [ToolName]Context = createContext<[ToolName]ContextType | undefined>(
  undefined
);
```

#### 3.4 Add to ToolAbstracts

```tsx
const ToolAbstracts = useMemo(() => {
  return [
    // ... existing tools
    {
      id: "[tool-name]",
      name: "[Tool Name]",
      description: "[Tool description]",
      icon: <[IconComponent] className="w-3.5 h-3.5" />,
    },
  ];
}, []);
```

#### 3.5 Add to memoizedTools

```tsx
const memoizedTools = useMemo(
  () => [
    // ... existing tools
    {
      id: "[tool-name]",
      name: "[Tool Name]",
      description: "[Tool description]",
      icon: <[IconComponent] className="w-3.5 h-3.5" />,
      onClick: () => {
        if (activeTool?.id === "[tool-name]") return;
        createToolClickHandler("/Tool/[ToolName]", "[tool-name]")();
      },
      href: "/Tool/[ToolName]",
    },
  ],
  [createToolClickHandler]
);
```

#### 3.6 Add Context Provider (if widget)

If it's a widget, add the context provider:

```tsx
const [toolName]Value: [ToolName]ContextType = useMemo(
  () => ({
    showState: memoizedOsSettings.[toolName],
    isMounted,
  }),
  [memoizedOsSettings.[toolName], isMounted]
);

// In the return statement, add:
<[ToolName]Context.Provider value={[toolName]Value}>
  {/* other providers */}
</[ToolName]Context.Provider>
```

#### 3.7 Export Hook (if widget)

```tsx
export const use[ToolName]OS = () => {
  const context = useContext([ToolName]Context);
  if (!context) {
    throw new Error("use[ToolName]OS must be used within an OSProvider");
  }
  return context;
};
```

### 4. Add to VirtualRouter

#### 4.1 Create Virtual Component

In `components/Tool/VirtualToolComponents.tsx`:

```tsx
// Add import if needed
import { [IconComponent] } from "lucide-react"; // or appropriate icon library

// Add virtual component
export const Virtual[ToolName]: React.FC = () => (
  <VirtualToolBase
    toolName="[Tool Name]"
    description="[Tool description]"
    icon={<[IconComponent] />}
  />
);
```

#### 4.2 Register in MainLayout

In `layouts/MainLayout.tsx`:

```tsx
// Add import
import {
  // ... existing imports
  Virtual[ToolName],
} from "$/components/Tool/VirtualToolComponents";

// Add to virtualRoutes array
const virtualRoutes = [
  // ... existing routes
  {
    path: "/Tool/[ToolName]",
    component: Virtual[ToolName],
    name: "[Tool Name]",
  },
];
```

### 5. Add to STATIC_TOOL_ROUTES

In `OS/Provider/OSProv.tsx`, add to the `STATIC_TOOL_ROUTES` array:

```tsx
const STATIC_TOOL_ROUTES = [
  // ... existing routes
  "/Tool/[ToolName]",
];
```

## Complete Example: Statistics Tool

Here's a real example from the Statistics tool:

### File Structure

```
components/Tool/Statistics/
├── index.tsx
├── provider/
│   └── statisticsProvider.tsx
└── components/
    ├── StatisticsContainer.tsx
    └── ContributionHeatmap.tsx
```

### Key Points

1. **Naming Convention**: Use PascalCase for component names, camelCase for IDs and variables
2. **Provider Pattern**: Always use a provider for state management and app schema
3. **InteractApp**: Wrap main content with `InteractApp` to enable sidebar, dialogs, etc.
4. **Virtual Router**: Essential for instant navigation - must be registered
5. **SEO Schema**: Include comprehensive SEO metadata in the page file
6. **Icon Selection**: Use appropriate icons from `lucide-react` or `react-icons`

## Testing Checklist

- [ ] Tool appears in OS menu
- [ ] Clicking tool navigates correctly
- [ ] Virtual component shows during navigation
- [ ] Page loads with correct layout
- [ ] Provider context works correctly
- [ ] App schema (sidebar, dialogs) functions properly
- [ ] SEO metadata is correct
- [ ] No console errors

## Common Patterns

### For Widget Tools (Draggable)

- Add to `OSSettings` interface
- Create context type extending `BaseWidgetContextType`
- Add context provider in OSProv
- Export `use[ToolName]OS` hook

### For Page-Only Tools

- Skip widget context setup
- Focus on page and provider setup
- Still need VirtualRouter registration

### For Tools with Sidebar

- Define `sidebar.sections` in `appSchema`
- Use `menuItem` helper for context menus
- Implement drag-and-drop if needed

## Notes

- Always follow the existing patterns in the codebase
- Use TypeScript strictly - avoid `any` types
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility
- Use memoization for expensive computations
- Follow the design system (Shadcn UI, Tailwind CSS)
- Ensure accessibility and responsive design
